# Git workflow (d3)

Full patterns and examples: **`.cursor/prompts/git-conventions-workflow.md`**. PR structure must match **`.github/pull_request_template.md`**.

## Branches

- Shape: `<type>-<summary>` or `issue-<n>/<type>-<summary>`.
- **Types:** `fix`, `feature`, `doc`, `shore`, `ci`, `update`.
- Summary: kebab-case, specific (never bare `fix` / `shore` / `doc`).

## Commits

- Imperative mood, short title first; add body only when needed.
- Avoid verbose or “this commit” boilerplate.

## Pull requests

- Fill every section the template expects (Summary, Type of change, checklists, Breaking changes, Testing, Compatibility / docs).
- Tie Summary to real branch changes; use `Fixes #` / `Closes #` when an issue applies.
